'''Francis Steegmuller''' (July 3, 1906 <U+2013> October 20, 1994) was an American biographer, translator and fiction writer, who was known chiefly as a [[Flaubert]] scholar.<ref>{{cite web|title=NNDB|url=http://www.nndb.com/people/077/000117723/ }}</ref>

==Life and career==
Born in [[New Haven, Connecticut]], Steegmuller graduated from [[Columbia University]] in 1927.<ref name=fspapers/> He contributed numerous short stories and articles to ''[[The New Yorker]]'' and also wrote under the pseudonyms of Byron Steel and David Keith. He won two [[National Book Award]]s<U+2014>one in 1971 for [[List of winners of the National Book Award#Arts and Letters|Arts and Letters]] for his biography of [[Jean Cocteau]] (''Cocteau: A Biography''),<ref name=nba1971>
[http://www.nationalbook.org/nba1971.html "National Book Awards <U+2013> 1971"]. [[National Book Foundation]]. Retrieved 2012-03-10.</ref> another in 1981 for [[List of winners of the National Book Award#Translation|Translation]] for the first volume of Flaubert's complete letters (''The Letters of Gustave Flaubert 1830-1857'')<ref name=nba1981>
[http://www.nationalbook.org/nba1981.html "National Book Awards <U+2013> 1981"]. [[National Book Foundation]]. Retrieved 2012-03-10.</ref><U+2014>and the [[American Academy of Arts and Letters Gold Medal]]. His first wife was Beatrice Stein, a painter who was a pupil and friend of [[Jacques Villon]]; she died in 1961. He married the writer [[Shirley Hazzard]] in 1963. His collected papers are held at two universities: at [[Yale University]], the [[James Jackson Jarves]] (1818<U+2013>1888) Papers and the [http://hdl.handle.net/10079/fa/beinecke.steeg Francis Steegmuller Collection for Jacques Villon]; at [[Columbia University]], the [http://www.columbia.edu/cu/lweb/eresources/archives/collections/html/4079364.html Francis Steegmuller Papers 1877<U+2013>1979].<ref name=fspapers>{{cite web | title=Francis Steegmuller Papers 1877-1979 | work=Columbia University Libraries | url=http://www.columbia.edu/cu/libraries/inside/projects/findingaids/scans/pdfs/42_STE-SY_02.pdf | accessdate=2006-05-22}}</ref>

